<br>
“Have you been treated unwell here?”<br>
<br>
“No, I ---”<br>
<br>
“Lucas,” he interrupted with a growl.  “Your love for him causes you to betray your parents’ wishes?”<br>
<br>
“I don’t *love* him,” she argued.  “He’s my friend.  That’s it.”<br>
<br>
“I ---”<br>
<br>
“Like I said, I just want to go home.  It doesn’t have anything to do with you or any member of your family.”<br>
<br>
Alexander seemed surprised by her statement, but he nodded as if he came to some kind of inner understanding.<br>
<br>
“You miss your family.”<br>
<br>
“Yes,” she answered.  Alexander nodded again.<br>
<br>
“We shall return to your home soon after we are wed,” he said definitively, leaving no room for objection.  <br>
<br>
“But ---”<br>
<br>
